<item>
            <title>[LU-12903] lctl-pcc man page does not exist</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12903</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The man page for lctl-pcc does not exist on the Lustre client. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[root@trevis-62vm8 ~]# man lctl-pcc
No manual entry for lctl-pcc
[root@trevis-62vm8 ~]# man lctl_pcc
No manual entry for lctl_pcc
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yet, &#8216;man lfs-pcc&#8217; says it should exist. From the lfs-pcc man page:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;      SEE ALSO
              lfs(1), lfs-hsm(1), lfs-pcc-detach(1), lctl-pcc(8)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue is that &#8216;lctl-pcc&#8217; does not exist in the lustre/doc/Makefile.am file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like the following are also missing:&lt;br/&gt;
lctl-pcc.8&lt;br/&gt;
lfs-pcc-detach.1&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_attach.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_attach_fid.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_attach_fid_str.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_detach_fid.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_detach_fid_fd.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_detach_fid_str.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_detach_file.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pccdev_get.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pccdev_set.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_state_get.3&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_pcc_state_get_fd.3&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
